Police recovered 24 firearms and two explosive devices during a raid in Weenen, KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. Kwazulu-Natal police spokesperson, Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo said on Monday morning police approached an identified house at Manqofini area to conduct a search operation. Ngcobo said: Ngcobo said during the search of the house police recovered a shotgun, two rifles, a revolver, four pistols and ninety rounds of ammunition. Police also found two explosives devices, a vehicle engine and dagga inside the house, she said. Ngcobo said police then moved on to another house in the Sahlumbe area where they recovered one rifle and 15 pistols. "Unfortunately the suspects fled prior to the arrival of police," said Ngcobo.Â In total, eight suspects aged between 20 and 46 were arrested and detained at Weenen police station. They were charged with attempted murder, possession of dagga, unlawful possession of explosives as well as unlawful possession of firearms and ammunition. They are expected to appear before the Weenen Magistrates Court on Wednesday.